translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_69e1bd57:
    # "Sarah looked out over the edge of the cart, spying through the metal bars that kept her trapped inside."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_cc4b43f0:
    # "She had known for a while that they had been drawing closer to Al'Gahaem, the sounds of the city had been carried on the wind, meeting them as they neared the city."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_b29aca69:
    # "Before, all she could see was the same, from day to day. Desert, stretching out as far as the horizon."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_b629a83a:
    # "She was recently sure they had been on the road for a little over two weeks, but one day bled into the next, and with little distraction, she dared not even be certain of that."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_c392e4a9:
    # "But now distraction was all she could see."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_603164c0:
    # "Al'Gahaem was truly a city, and yet, so very different from the capital in Rosanna."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d0ea8ef3:
    # "The cart rode across a broad stone brick road which was so full it had to stop on more than on occasion."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_08893580:
    # "On each end of the large road, tents, hovels and the rare sandstone house, all weaved together."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_e6947517:
    # "As if the city was some chaotic thing, alive in the way that a beehive could be called alive. All across it, the people swarmed and moved, seemingly random, and yet, each with purpose."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_6fc7e3a7:
    # "Sarah quickly concluded that Al'Gahaem was a city which existed by success."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_650de872:
    # "Unlike the capital in Rosanna, which stood for centuries, seeing good times and bad times but always persisting, Al'Gahaem spawned out of the succes of Hassar's conquests."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_e7287807:
    # "And just as easily, she figured, it would likely fade back into the desert should the good times end."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_ef1ec7eb:
    # "This was a city that existed because it willed to exist and needed to exist."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_053121bc:
    # "And so roads were construced, tents build, hovels quickly put up, all growing organically to the surging demand."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_bc88392e:
    # "Passing by a building on the side of the road, Sarah saw a crowd of people, waving up their hands, shouting out bids."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_ace424fc:
    # "On the stage, she saw five people, each close to her age, chained to the wooden floor, naked save for the shackles that kept them their."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_0f06f23e:
    # "Each seemed to have the same defeated look on their face, mostly staring down or out into the vague distance."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_774b8855:
    # "Even naked, it was obvious to Sarah. These were her countrymen, being sold as slaves."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_b26fe3fb:
    # "Al'Gahaem was as city that grew no crops, mined no ores, and had no industry to speak of. They existed off their plunder, which meant above all other things, slaves."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_3abfba75:
    # "Sarah felt a sting of pain in her heart."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_0bb8c21b:
    # "To bear the fate that had fallen on her was one thing, but to know that so many in her nation now suffered like she did, it was enough to tear her apart."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_9b0572f8:
    # "She sat back down, having seen enough of this horrid city for now. She tried to find comfort in feeling of the cart weaving from side to side."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_502ed315:
    # "Some time later, they came to a halt."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_450eadf3:
    # "The sounds of the city had grown louder and louder. Sarah suspected they were drawing close to somewhere."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_724992f4:
    # "The door to the wagon opened."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_4d1f090c:
    # "The officer stood in the opening, he had a distracted look on his face."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_dac9eeb3:
    # "Off to the side, he was shouting commands at some men. He snapped his finger at Sarah, urging her to come to him. She dutifully did."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_283e84c0:
    # "Jaeid stood in the opening, a stern look on his face."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_b28b002e:
    # j "Sarah, we've arrived."
    j ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_56140f2b:
    # s "Arrived where?"
    s ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_ce1c578b:
    # j "The house of the Khan, Hassar's palace."
    j ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_5bc31e7a:
    # s "What do you want me to do?"
    s ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_5b8b6854:
    # "Sarah begged him with her eyes for any help he could offer her."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d16a8ee4:
    # j "Trust in me, in what I've told you, and you will be fine."
    j ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_2239051d:
    # "She knew she had no other options."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_8df6dc98:
    # "She pushed herself off the wooden floor of the cart and walked towards Jaeid."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_1072d5bd:
    # s "I know, appearances."
    s ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_9f99ff72:
    # "She said it and turned around, letting him seize her by the arm. She could feel he tried to be gentle with her."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d5442fca:
    # "Under the watchful eye of her chaperone, she stepped out of the cart."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_6b921a99:
    # "All around her, people were rushing off in different directions. Busy. Everything was so busy here."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_76796b1a:
    # "What most surprised her was how little she seemed to matter to any of them."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d352c366:
    # "A naked woman in Rosanna would bring the street to a stop, but here, she barely seemed to solicit more than a quick appreciative glance."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_a63e0c2f:
    # "The hand around her arm pulled on her, reminding her to keep walking."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_38ac9dfc:
    # "Out in front of her was the great palace."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d8e602ed:
    # "It lived up to its name."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_74774607:
    # "The palace was oddly flat, with the exclusion of several spires off the corners of the construction, reaching up to the heavens."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_e5c99b62:
    # "But for the lack of its height, it made up by stretching far beyond even Sarah could see."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_a4f6b718:
    # "Build entirely out of sandstone, the great palace seemed almost as if it had been carved out of the earth itself. Sarah wondered, if that might not just have been the case."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_d6100ac6:
    # "As she was dragged up the stairs, Sarah tried her best to keep up with the march, keeping her balance with every step."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_bfdf7451:
    # "The people leaving and entering the great palace were like a surge in both directions. One misstep and Sarah figured they would carry her off like the current in the sea."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_82f40c3b:
    # "Stepping into the castle, a cooling shade descended on her skin."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_42b0811b:
    # "There were few windows, leaving the great palace feeling oddly muted in its colours, but also keeping the punishing desert heat out."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInAlGahaem_4884bd9f:
    # "Sarah was grateful for this fact, because she doubted she could survive even a single day of full exposure to this sun."
